hīnayāna   is a sanskrit term literally meaning : the " smaller vehicle",kalu rinpoche ( 1995 ) profound buddhism from hinayana to vajrayana : p. 15 applied to the śrāvakayāna , the buddhist path followed by a śrāvaka who wishes to become an arhat .

religion : mahayanists label other schools of this religion " hinayana " or " lesser vehicle "

